   =20
      ChatGPT
   =20
 =20

The  stereotype of chat-based large-language-model artificial intelligence =
products in early 2023 is that they are very good at sounding smart but not=
 so good at being correct. If you ask a model like ChatGPT to write up some=
 investment recommendations, it will produce plausible fluent prose that re=
ads like a professional investment recommendation and that includes compell=
ing citations to data points, but the data might be all made up=C2=A0and th=
e recommendations might be worthless. It is good enough to convince the uni=
nformed, but not good enough to act on.
Given that stereotype, you might=C2=A0imagine two ways for big banks to thi=
nk about these models:
=09=E2=80=9CBeing fluent, confident and wrong is a core job function of a b=
anker or investment analyst, and ChatGPT allows our employees to be much mo=
re efficient at it, so we should encourage them to use ChatGPT as much as p=
ossible.=E2=80=9D=09=E2=80=9COur clients will be annoyed with us if we are =
constantly fluent, confident and wrong, so we should ban use of ChatGPT unt=
il we are more confident that its recommendations are correct.=E2=80=9D

Obviously the first approach would be very funny, but   the second is more =
realistic. But in fact there is a third, less obvious, but even more correc=
t way for big banks to think about the use of these models:
=09=E2=80=9CIf our employees type about business on a computer or a phone, =
it had better be in a software system that we control and that creates a se=
archable record that we can preserve forever, because otherwise our regulat=
ors will get mad at us. ChatGPT is an artificial intelligence model, but it=
 is also a box for typing on a computer, and that=E2=80=99s too big a regul=
atory risk for us.=E2=80=9D

Bloomberg=E2=80=99s=C2=A0Gabriela Mello, William Shaw and Hannah Levitt  re=
port:

Wall Street is clamping down on ChatGPT as a slew of global investment bank=
s impose restrictions on the fast-growing technology that generates text in=
 response to a short prompt.=C2=A0
Bank of America Corp., Citigroup Inc., Deutsche Bank AG, Goldman Sachs Grou=
p Inc. and Wells Fargo & Co. are among lenders that have recently banned us=
age of the new tool, with Bank of America telling employees that ChatGPT an=
d openAI are prohibited from business use, according to people with knowled=
ge of the matter.=C2=A0
In a regular, routine reminder of unauthorized apps including WhatsApp, Bof=
A added a reference to ChatGPT specifically, and has repeated in internal m=
eetings that new technology must be vetted before it can be used in busines=
s communications, the people said.

We have  talked a few  times=C2=A0about the US Securities and Exchange Comm=
ission=E2=80=99s crackdown on banks that use anything other than =E2=80=9Co=
fficial channels=E2=80=9D to do business: If you text a client from your pe=
rsonal phone, or send her a WhatsApp message, that will get you and your ba=
nk in trouble. Not that you texted her about doing crimes, I mean, but send=
ing perfectly innocent businesslike communications over=C2=A0unofficial cha=
nnels will get you in trouble. You=E2=80=99re still allowed to talk about b=
usiness in person, over lunch, but give it time. I  wrote earlier this mont=
h:
In like five years, technology =E2=80=94 and the SEC=E2=80=99s interpretati=
on of the rules =E2=80=94 will have advanced to the point that banks will g=
et fined if their bankers talk about business with clients on the golf cour=
se. =E2=80=9CYou should have been wearing your bank-issued virtual reality =
headset and recorded the conversation,=E2=80=9D the SEC will say, or I gues=
s =E2=80=9Cyou should have played golf in your bank=E2=80=99s official meta=
verse, which records all golf conversations for compliance review, rather t=
han on a physical golf course.=E2=80=9D The golf course is an unofficial ch=
annel! No business allowed!
Well, similarly. If you want to get advice from a robot about how to invest=
 =E2=80=94=C2=A0or if you want the robot to help you write a presentation f=
or clients =E2=80=94=C2=A0then you had better communicate with the robot us=
ing official channels! Typing in the ChatGPT box isn=E2=80=99t an official =
channel, so it's not allowed.

