0P2NtcGlkPUJCRDAyMjcyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT=
1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDIyNyZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07=
ceef4b8524a319a23cB73eb10a1" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope"=
 target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importan=
t; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-st=
yle: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> stereotype</a> of chat-based large-la=
nguage-model artificial intelligence products in early 2023 is that they ar=
e very good at sounding smart but not so good at being correct. If you ask =
a model like ChatGPT to write up some investment recommendations, it will p=
roduce plausible fluent prose that reads like a professional investment rec=
ommendation and that includes compelling citations to data points, but the =
data might be all made up=C2=A0and the recommendations might be worthless. =
It is good enough to convince the uninformed, but not good enough to act on=
.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Given that stereotype, you might=C2=A0imagine =
two ways for big banks to think about these models:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">=E2=80=9CBeing fluent, confident and w=
rong is a core job function of a banker or investment analyst, and ChatGPT =
allows our employees to be much more efficient at it, so we should encourag=
e them to use ChatGPT as much as possible.=E2=80=9D</li>=09<li style=3D"mar=
gin-bottom: 5px;">=E2=80=9COur clients will be annoyed with us if we are co=
nstantly fluent, confident and wrong, so we should ban use of ChatGPT until=
 we are more confident that its recommendations are correct.=E2=80=9D</li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Obviously the first approach would be very fun=
ny, but <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30672977.2=
61430/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDItMjQvd=
2FsbC1zdHJlZXQtcy1jaGF0Z3B0LW5pZ2h0bWFyZS1zY2VuYXJpby1nZXRzLWEtcmVhbGl0eS1j=
aGVjaz9jbXBpZD1CQkQwMjI3MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3V=
yY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzAyMjcmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/60=
7f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBe5683598" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsc=
ope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impo=
rtant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-botto=
m-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  the second is more realistic</a>=
. But in fact there is a third, less obvious, but even more correct way for=
 big banks to think about the use of these models:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">=E2=80=9CIf our employees type about b=
usiness on a computer or a phone, it had better be in a software system tha=
t we control and that creates a searchable record that we can preserve fore=
ver, because otherwise our regulators will get mad at us. ChatGPT is an art=
ificial intelligence model, but it is also a box for typing on a computer, =
and that=E2=80=99s too big a regulatory risk for us.=E2=80=9D</li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Bloomberg=E2=80=99s=C2=A0Gabriela Mello, Willi=
am Shaw and Hannah Levitt <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.co=
m/click/30672977.261430/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGV=
zLzIwMjMtMDItMjQvY2l0aWdyb3VwLWdvbGRtYW4tc2FjaHMtam9pbi1jaGF0Z3B0LWNyYWNrZG=
93bi1mbi1yZXBvcnRzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAyMjcyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1ha=
WwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDIyNyZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9u=
ZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB6b1b4965" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemsc=
ope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoratio=
n: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000;=
 border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> report</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Wall Street is clamping down on ChatGPT as a s=
lew of global investment banks impose restrictions on the fast-growing tech=
nology that generates text in response to a short prompt.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Bank of America Corp., Citigroup Inc., Deutsch=
e Bank AG, Goldman Sachs Group Inc. and Wells Fargo &amp; Co. are among len=
ders that have recently banned usage of the new tool, with Bank of America =
telling employees that ChatGPT and openAI are prohibited from business use,=
 according to people with knowledge of the matter.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In a regular, routine reminder of unauthorized=
 apps including WhatsApp, BofA added a reference to ChatGPT specifically, a=
nd has repeated in internal meetings that new technology must be vetted bef=
ore it can be used in business communications, the people said.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We have <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/30672977.261430/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGlu=
aW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDktMjgvdGhlLWRlbGktd2FzLWFsbGVnZWRseS1hLWZyYXVkP2N=
